    {
        "content": "<p>mkatychev created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12827#discussion_r2978096761\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>From Google Books, it looks as if the -rr- spelling was more common in the nineteenth century and earlier. There are a small number of contemporary hits for -rr-, but they are vastly outweighed by the spelling with one R.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>From a bit of research, either way is fine though.</p>\n</blockquote>",
