    {
        "content": "<p>pchickey <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12827#issuecomment-4121682449\">commented</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12827\">PR #12827</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Thanks, its nice to have all these fixed and even nicer that there is a tool for automating this sort of toil. The <code>typos</code> crate docs says that false positives are low enough to run as part of PR CI checks. Would you mind adding that to our CI as part of this PR? Worst case, if it gets to be a burden, we can turn it off and come up with some other way to periodically clean the repo up.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 581480059,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1774389641
    },
    {
